<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3731.3.6>
    bibo:endPage "380" ;
    bibo:issue "3" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "371" ;
    bibo:volume "3731" ;
    dc:creator "Evenhuis, Neal L." ;
    dc:date "2013" ;
    dc:title "New microbombyliids (Diptera: Mythicomyiidae) from Eocene Baltic and Rovno ambers, with notes on previously described amber species" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.216392>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.216394> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.216392>
    dc:description "FIGURES 5 – 12. Antennae and wings of amber fossil Mythicomyiidae. Figs. 5 – 9. Antennae: 5, Glabellula brunnifrons Evenhuis; 6, Glabellula electrica (Hennig); 7, Glabellula perkovskyi, n. sp.; 8, Glabellula kuehnei Schlüter. 9, Riga toni, n. sp. Figs. 10 – 12. Wings: 10, Glabellula perkovskyi, n. sp.; 11, Carmenelectra pernigra, n. sp.; 12, Riga toni, n. sp." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/216392/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.216394>
    dc:description "FIGURES 15 – 18. Amber mythicomyiids. Figs. 15 – 16. Carmenelectra pernigra, n. sp.: 15, amber piece showing position of holotype. 16, Detail of holotype female. Fig. 17, Carmenelectra shehuggme, n. sp., detail of holotype. Fig. 18. Riga toni, n. sp., detail of holotype female." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/216394/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

